“The whole reason we plan this is because kids ride down that hill laughing and having a great time,” Heart of Biddeford Director Delilah Poupore said. “That’s the whole purpose of WinterFest.” 

All day Saturday, families are encouraged not only to sled but to enjoy giant outdoor games, free snacks and a ball pit.

For those who would rather stay warm and dry, there are plenty of exciting indoor activities throughout the weekend. 

Heart of Biddeford will host “The Big Chill,” a business expo and art event with music, dancing and winter nightlife at the Pepperell Center from noon to 10 p.m. Saturday. 

Across the street at City Theater, Elton John and Billy Joel cover band Piano Men will take the stage Friday night, while comedian Juston McKinney gets the crowd laughing Saturday. 

“The highlight of WinterFest is that there’s something for everyone,” Poupore said. 

