WinterFest isn’t just for the kids. On Friday night, grownups are invited for an adults-only sledding night followed by an afterparty social at Brickyard Hollow. 

Above all, Poupore said, it’s a good opportunity to explore Biddeford during the height of winter.

“It’s a time of the year that people tend to stay home and hunker down because their couch is so warm and comfortable,” she said. “WinterFest is cabin fever-busting.”

Most WinterFest events are free and open to the public. Admission for the adult sledding event is $10, with reservations available [on the Biddeford Recreation website](https://biddefordme.myrec.com/info/products/default.aspx).

Tickets for the Piano Men performance and McKinney’s comedy show are $35 each and available [via the city’s website](https://www.biddefordmaine.org/5687/WinterFest) or by calling the City Theater box office at 207-282-0849.

